WEBVTT

NOTE Alexandria Here Build Week demo — English captions

00:00:00.258 --> 00:00:01.790
The web forgets by accident.

00:00:02.286 --> 00:00:06.228
Alexandria Here is a witnessed
restoration engine for the lost web.

00:00:06.713 --> 00:00:10.903
It does not generate the past;
it reconciles surviving witnesses.

00:00:11.432 --> 00:00:15.450
This is iExile, the literary community
I founded in 2007,

00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:18.647
returned from public archive evidence.

00:00:19.154 --> 00:00:21.543
Give Alexandria one public URL.

00:00:22.039 --> 00:00:24.054
When connected evidence is sufficient,

00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:29.083
it opens directly into a coherent
returned site—not a screenshot gallery.

00:00:29.608 --> 00:00:33.000
This edition passed through the same
bounded live-recovery pipeline

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:34.878
available to every visitor.

00:00:35.374 --> 00:00:38.600
It returns five visible pages
from eight capture records

00:00:38.600 --> 00:00:41.442
spanning August through November 2009.

00:00:41.926 --> 00:00:44.052
Its centerpiece is challengeability.

00:00:44.534 --> 00:00:47.366
Show the Seams exposes
block-level provenance.

00:00:47.877 --> 00:00:52.642
Every rendered historical block resolves
to archived evidence and a content hash.

00:00:53.124 --> 00:00:55.928
Alexandria may reconstruct placement,

00:00:56.092 --> 00:00:59.449
but it cannot display unsupported
historical content.

00:00:59.944 --> 00:01:02.882
If a page is known only through
surviving links,

00:01:03.086 --> 00:01:04.849
the absence remains visible.

00:01:05.359 --> 00:01:08.389
The Temporal Evidence Graph reconciles
capture dates,

00:01:08.626 --> 00:01:09.900
URL variants, conflicts,

00:01:10.060 --> 00:01:13.987
and source relationships
into one supported edition.

00:01:14.476 --> 00:01:16.945
The Ghost Map reveals
the shape of survival:

00:01:17.256 --> 00:01:22.300
returned pages, inferred connections,
and eight known absences—paths

00:01:22.300 --> 00:01:23.898
witnessed by the archive,

00:01:24.046 --> 00:01:25.767
but not faithfully recoverable.

00:01:26.266 --> 00:01:28.811
Every recovery ends with
a mechanical receipt.

00:01:29.367 --> 00:01:32.585
This one discloses planner GPT-5.6,

00:01:32.733 --> 00:01:34.754
model GPT-5.6-sol,

00:01:34.888 --> 00:01:38.139
946 source hashes, 347 rendered blocks,

00:01:38.417 --> 00:01:43.106
and ten of ten passing validations.

00:01:43.654 --> 00:01:46.786
The model proposes consequential
evidence choices;

00:01:46.964 --> 00:01:49.400
deterministic code derives
the cited structure

00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:51.763
and decides what may be rendered.

00:01:52.356 --> 00:01:53.623
Failure stays visible.

00:01:54.150 --> 00:01:56.462
Silence is never filled with fiction.

00:01:56.947 --> 00:02:00.307
Codex served as the build integrator
across architecture,

00:02:00.578 --> 00:02:03.894
archive retrieval, hostile HTML handling,

00:02:04.064 --> 00:02:06.929
temporal reasoning, security, tests,

00:02:07.196 --> 00:02:09.218
deployment, and browser audits.

00:02:09.738 --> 00:02:11.088
Inside the shipped product,

00:02:11.224 --> 00:02:14.140
GPT-5.6 is the Chronologist.

00:02:14.641 --> 00:02:19.261
It receives a bounded evidence packet
and returns only a strict schema:

00:02:19.458 --> 00:02:22.704
visible-page order and
primary witness IDs.

00:02:23.211 --> 00:02:24.387
It is consequential,

00:02:24.566 --> 00:02:26.388
but never allowed to write history.

00:02:26.855 --> 00:02:30.115
Alexandria Here returns a
place—with witnesses.

00:02:30.647 --> 00:02:31.538
The lost web,

00:02:31.679 --> 00:02:34.837
present again, without pretending
the gaps were never there.
